    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required levels. The Test conditions factor achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; however, the team judged this shortfall acceptable given the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol and strong quantitative agreement across all QoIs (all E/uval < 1.96, all QoI differences <10%). Overall assurance level declared High based on the breadth of evidence and multi-laboratory confirmation. Submission accepted for regulatory review.",
